description.narrative: UNICEF, in partnership with the Ministry of Education (MoE), continue to make progress towards the basic education targets of access, quality and inclusion for all children. During the first two quarters of 2020, in particular the second quarter, programme delivery was significantly impacted by COVID-19 pandemics, slowing the implementation rate and requiring adaptation, where possible, of implementation modality. Programme continuity was achieved especially in the conflict-affected Rakhine State through Learning Together initiative. Simultaneously, UNICEF has been supporting the government's COVID-19 response and recovery initiatives aiming at the learning resumption and continuity of the most disadvantaged children. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/07/2020
